Java is a high-level, object-oriented programming language.
It was first released by Sun Microsystems in 1995.
Java is widely used for developing cross-platform applications.
Java programs are compiled into bytecode, which can run on any platform with a JVM installed.
Java's syntax is similar to that of C++ and other programming languages.
Java's memory management is automatic, making it less error-prone and more secure.
Java's extensive standard library provides a wide range of built-in functions and APIs.
Java is used for developing web and mobile applications, enterprise software, games, and more.
